# Project Context

- Start with `project.config.json` to understand the project name, slug, preset, domain, owner team and generation path.
- Use `cursor/context-map.md` as the quick map of the generated project structure.
- For frontend work, read `cursor/projects/frontend/project-context.md` before changing `frontend/**`.
- For backend work, read `cursor/projects/backend/project-context.md` before changing `backend/**`.
- For infrastructure work, read `cursor/projects/infrastructure/project-context.md` before changing `infrastructure/**`.
- For cross-stack work, read all relevant project contexts and check whether contracts, mocks, docs and tests need updates.
- Use `cursor/docs/AI-Project-Playbook.md` for the expected intake, analysis, implementation, testing and review flow.

